==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Damnify
<hw>Dam"ni*fy</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧m"n⟦icr⟧*f⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[LL. <ets>damnificare</ets>, fr. L. <ets>damnificus</ets>: cf. OF.
<ets>damnefier</ets>. See <er>Damnific</er>.]</ety> <def>To cause loss
or damage to; to injure; to impair.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This work will ask as many more officials to make expurgations and
expunctions, that the commonwealth of learning be not
<qex>damnified</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Damning</ent>⟦br⟧
